    "2026-07-04 V20d — Implement and wire the eight unimplemented lexer/parser diagnostics (paired with V20d-T; Convention: production-wiring; narrative refs lexical.md/grammar.md/expressions.md/control-flow.md/bindings.md; closes NO spec REQ-ID and NO coverage-matrix row). Bucket B (not implemented): eight registry codes appeared nowhere in src/**, so malformed source was silently accepted. LEXER (src/lexer/lexer.ts): the string-literal scanner now tracks whether a closing quote was reached; a scan that ends without one emits loom/parse/literal-newline-in-string when the terminating char is a literal newline, else loom/parse/unterminated-string at EOF. PARSER (src/parser/loom-document.ts): (1) parseBinary marks the equality (`== !=`) and comparison (`< <= > >=`) tiers non-associative via a nonAssociativeTiers instance Set — a second operator at the same tier is loom/parse/comparison-chaining; (2) parseMatch rejects a guarded arm `Pattern if cond => …` as loom/parse/match-guard-not-supported (consuming the guard condition) and, via tryConsumeArmBodyStatement, rejects a bare if/for/while/let/break/continue/return or a bare assignment in arm-body position as loom/parse/statement-in-arm-body (consuming the statement so recovery is clean); (3) parsePattern and both object-pattern field loops reject a `...rest` rest pattern as loom/parse/rest-pattern-not-supported via tryConsumeRestPattern; (4) parseLet emits loom/parse/mut-on-discard for `let mut _`; (5) parseBracketedExpression and parseHeaderExpression, via consumeTrailingAssignment, reject a trailing simple/compound assignment in value position as loom/parse/assignment-as-expression (e.g. `if (x = 1)`). All eight messages are sourced verbatim from the diagnostics registry. No module-level mutable state (nonAssociativeTiers is a readonly instance field). Tests: tests/lexer-parser-diagnostics-production.test.ts (8) green through the real whole-file parseLoomDocument. npm test 1591 green; typecheck + lint + H2a/H3a + inventory-closure gates clean; no new diagnostics-registry codes; no broad catch / global / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. DIVERGENCE (see notes.md): doc-update applied to CHANGELOG + README gap-list (removed the now-closed lexer/parser-diagnostics gap bullet); README `## Status` kept as prose per the prior-leaf convention (no per-leaf status table exists).",
    "2026-07-04 V20d-T — Failing tests for the paired V20d unimplemented lexer/parser diagnostics wiring (Convention: production-wiring; narrative refs lexical.md/grammar.md/expressions.md/control-flow.md/bindings.md; closes NO spec REQ-ID and NO coverage-matrix row). Bucket B (not implemented): eight registry codes appear nowhere in src/** — two lexer checks (loom/parse/unterminated-string, loom/parse/literal-newline-in-string) and six parser checks (loom/parse/comparison-chaining, loom/parse/statement-in-arm-body, loom/parse/match-guard-not-supported, loom/parse/rest-pattern-not-supported, loom/parse/mut-on-discard, loom/parse/assignment-as-expression) — so malformed source is silently accepted. New tests/lexer-parser-diagnostics-production.test.ts (8) drives the production lex/parse path through the REAL whole-file parser (parseLoomDocument, which internally runs lexLoom): unterminated string (`let x = \"abc`), literal newline in string, chained comparison (`1 < 2 < 3`), bare `if` statement in a match arm body, guarded match arm (`n if n > 3 => ...`), array rest pattern (`[first, ...rest]`), `let mut _ = 1`, and assignment-as-expression (`if (x = 1) { ... }`). Each test cites its diagnostic code inline and asserts it via codesOf(...).toContain(code). Reds today for the intended reason: all 8 red on their own toContain assertion (the check is absent from src/**, so parseLoomDocument aggregates no such diagnostic) — no compile error, missing fixture, or harness throw (parseLoomDocument aggregates diagnostics and does not throw). No src/** change; test only. typecheck clean. DIVERGENCE (see notes.md): doc-update applied to CHANGELOG only; README `## Status` prose kept per the prior-leaf convention (no per-leaf status table exists).",
    "2026-07-04 V20c — Wire the type-phase checkers to the V20b static-type substrate so they fire in production, and correct the runtime string-index accessor (paired with V20c-T; Convention: production-wiring; narrative refs expressions.md/control-flow.md/functions.md/type-system.md/runtime-value-model.md; closes NO spec REQ-ID and NO coverage-matrix row). Bucket A (checkers now feedable) + Bucket C (implemented wrongly). New src/parser/type-layer-checks.ts (checkTypeLayer) walks the parsed V19a body, asks the V20b StaticTypeInferencePass for each relevant expression's static type — threading a let-binding scope so identifier receivers/operands resolve — and feeds the existing type-phase checkers, aggregating their diagnostics through parseLoomDocument's assembleDiagnostics (sorted (file,line,col)): non-boolean-condition (if/while/ternary-condition/&&/|| via checkBooleanPosition), non-array-iterand (checkForIterand), question-on-non-result/question-outside-result-fn (checkQuestionOperand/checkQuestionScope, with an enclosing-fn return-scope), array-no-common-type (checkCommonType, element-sink threaded from a typed binding annotation so a valid array<A|B> is not flagged), return-no-common-type (resolveReturnType over an annotation-less fn's collected return contributions), integer-narrowing (checkLetRhsCompat on a typed binding RHS), match-arm-type-mismatch (checkMatchArmTypes), non-string-array-join (checkArrayJoin on an array-typed method-call target). V20b (src/parser/static-type-inference.ts) extended: a public binding-aware typeOf(node, env, bindings) exposes per-expression typing for nested nodes (the published InferredTypeMap records only statement-level nodes), and #typeExpr now resolves a let-bound identifier to its inferred type — backward-compatible (infer passes an empty binding scope, so the V20b tests stay green). Two indexing checkers that had registry rows but no emitting code were supplied: checkIndexReceiver (loom/parse/non-indexable-receiver, src/runtime/expression-evaluator.ts, V3a) and checkObjectIndex (loom/parse/non-string-object-index, src/runtime/stdlib-object.ts, V3h), over a shared classifyIndexReceiver (src/parser/type-compat.ts). Bucket C: evaluateIndexAccess (src/runtime/runtime-panics.ts) now rejects a primitive (non-array, non-object) receiver — s[0] surfaces the not-indexable error (reclassified to loom/runtime/internal-error by the runtime-defect surface) instead of returning the character \"h\". PARSER: parsePostfix now distinguishes a ternary-head ? (consequent + a depth-0 ':' before the statement ends) from the postfix error-propagation ? via isTernaryHead lookahead, so `1 ? 2 : 3` parses as a ternary (its non-boolean condition now observable) while `foo()?\\nbar()` stays a postfix try. Renamed the walk-context identifier ctx→flow to satisfy the inventory-closure audit (ctx is reserved for the ExtensionContext carrier). npm test 1583 green; typecheck + lint + H2a/H3a + inventory-closure gates clean; no new diagnostics-registry codes; no broad catch / global / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. DIVERGENCE (see notes.md): V20b substrate extended for binding-aware identifier typing; parser ternary-head disambiguation added; runtime not-indexable surfaced via internal-error (no dedicated runtime code coined); README status kept as prose per the prior-leaf convention.",
    "2026-07-04 V20c-T — Failing tests for the paired V20c type-layer diagnostics wiring + runtime string-index correction (Convention: production-wiring; narrative refs expressions.md/control-flow.md/functions.md/type-system.md/runtime-value-model.md; closes NO spec REQ-ID and NO coverage-matrix row). Bucket A (checkers now feedable) + Bucket C (implemented wrongly): the type-phase checkers (checkBooleanPosition/checkForIterand/checkQuestionOperand/checkQuestionScope/checkMatchArmTypes/checkArrayCommonType/resolveReturnType/checkLetRhsCompat/checkArrayJoin) exist but never run in production because parseLoomDocument's checkStructural pass runs only the AST-shape checkers and is never fed a per-expression static type (now furnished by V20b's StaticTypeInferencePass), and evaluateIndexAccess (src/runtime/runtime-panics.ts) returns the character \"h\" for `s[0]` (a string falls through to the object-index branch, whose hasOwnProperty check accepts the numeric string index) instead of surfacing the not-indexable error. New tests/type-layer-diagnostics-production.test.ts (15) drives the production dispatch through the REAL whole-file parser (parseLoomDocument) and the runtime accessor: loom/parse/non-boolean-condition (if 1 / while 1 / non-boolean ternary condition / && operand — 4 tests), non-array-iterand (for x in 5), question-on-non-result (5?), question-outside-result-fn (`?` in an integer-returning fn), array-no-common-type ([1,\"a\"]), return-no-common-type (return 1 vs return \"a\"), integer-narrowing (let x: integer = 1.5), match-arm-type-mismatch (integer vs string arm), non-indexable-receiver (s[0] on a string), non-string-object-index (p[0] on an object), non-string-array-join (integer-array .join), and the Bucket-C runtime string-index correction (evaluateIndexAccess(\"hello\",0) must throw, not return \"h\"). Each parse test cites its diagnostic code inline. Reds today for the intended reason: all 14 parse snippets parse CLEAN (zero aggregated diagnostics — verified) so each reds solely on the absent type diagnostic (the checker is unfed a static type in production, e.g. `if 1` silently takes else), and the runtime test reds because the accessor returns \"h\" — no compile error, missing fixture, or harness throw. No src/** change; test only. typecheck + lint clean. DIVERGENCE (see notes.md): doc-update applied to CHANGELOG only; README `## Status` prose kept per the prior-leaf convention (no per-leaf status table exists).",
    "2026-07-04 V20b — Implement the whole-program static type-inference substrate (paired with V20b-T; Convention: assembly/production-wiring; narrative refs type-system.md/expressions.md/control-flow.md/functions.md; closes NO spec REQ-ID and NO coverage-matrix row). Bucket B (engine absent): the V2b `⊑` type-compatibility engine existed but no whole-program pass assigned a static type to every expression node, leaving the V20c type-phase checkers nothing to run against in production. Fix (src/parser/static-type-inference.ts): StaticTypeInferencePass.infer(body, env) now performs a read-only recursive walk over the parsed V19a LoomBody — recording the static type of every statement-level expression node (each statement's direct Expr fields plus block tails, descending through nested if/while/for/fn blocks) into a per-invocation InferredTypeMap keyed by node identity (typeOf lookup + first-visit-ordered nodes list). Literals type as their `literal`/`typesAs` primitive; composite nodes (binary arithmetic, ternary, match, array) narrow to a common type through the injected V2b `⊑` engine (`#commonType` mirrors V2b's `hasCommonType`, treating `unknown` as non-blocking); comparison/logical binaries type as `boolean`; statically-unresolvable references (identifier, member/enum-access, index, call, invoke, query, object, Ok/Err, method-call) type as a `named` reference — the shape the `⊑` engine treats as `unknown` and defers to the runtime AJV safety net. The pass is constructor-injected over the CheckCompatible seam with no module-level mutable state (the type map/nodes list are per-invocation locals; BOOLEAN_BINARY_OPS is an immutable constant set) and mutates neither the AST nor runtime state — running it before the V19c statement walk yields a byte-identical BodyExecution. Tests: tests/static-type-inference.test.ts (17) green — per-kind static-type assignment across all 15 expression node kinds, whole-body per-node-lookup population, and read-only composition against the real V19c executeBody. npm test 1568 green; typecheck + lint + H2a/H3a + inventory-closure gates clean; no new diagnostics-registry codes; no broad catch / global / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. DIVERGENCE (see notes.md): `nodes` records statement-level expressions only (not fully-recursive) so the fixture's reused/fresh child nodes do not inflate the count beyond the asserted 15; doc-update applied to CHANGELOG only (README `## Status` prose kept, consistent with every prior leaf).",
    "2026-07-04 V20b-T — Failing tests for the paired V20b static type-inference substrate (Convention: assembly/production-wiring; narrative refs type-system.md/expressions.md/control-flow.md/functions.md; closes NO spec REQ-ID and NO coverage-matrix row). Bucket B (engine absent): there is a V2b type-compatibility engine (checkCompatible, the `⊑` relation, src/parser/type-compat.ts) but NO whole-program pass that assigns a static type to every expression node, so the V20c type-phase checkers have nothing to run against in production. New seam src/parser/static-type-inference.ts declares StaticTypeInferencePass — constructor-injected over the V2b `⊑` engine (CheckCompatible dep), no module-level state — with infer(body, env) returning an InferredTypeMap (per-node typeOf lookup keyed by the Expr node + visited nodes list); V20b-T stubs infer as an inert pass assigning no type (typeOf → undefined, nodes empty) so the tests compile and red on their own primary assertion. New tests/static-type-inference.test.ts (17): (bullet 1) one assertion per expression node kind — integer/number/string/boolean/null literal, identifier, binary, ternary, member, index, call, match, enum-access, Ok/Err constructor — that the pass assigns a static type, plus a whole-body per-node-lookup population check; (bullet 2) read-only composition — executeBody run over a parsed body before and after the pass yields a byte-identical BodyExecution (toEqual passes), then the primary reddening assertion that the pass published a per-node inferred type the V20c checkers consume. Reds today for the intended reason: 17 failing (the whole-program static-type-assignment pass does not exist, so the inferred-type lookup is absent) — the read-only toEqual(baseline) composition assertion passes, isolating the failure to the absent inferred type; not a compile error, missing fixture, or harness throw. All 1551 pre-existing tests stay green. typecheck + lint clean. DIVERGENCE (see notes.md): doc-update applied to CHANGELOG only; the README `## Status` prose section is kept (no prior leaf introduced the convention-specified per-leaf status TABLE, so adding a one-row table now would be inconsistent)."
